== Roasted Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Halve,
peel, and cut @red onion{1} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until
you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss carrots and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces. (TIP: For a
smoother texture, peel potatoes first.) Place in a #medium pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Chicken ==

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.
Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until
you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

> Swap in pork* or steak* for chicken. Cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7
> minutes per side.

== Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add
minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is
softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings).
Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== Mashed Potatoes Finishing ==

Return pot with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add
@?sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash
with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking
liquid as needed. Season generously with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top chicken with
sauce and serve.

> Slice chicken or steak against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.